NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On transfer auctions, however, the person with longer trump suit is the dummy. So, only on those auctions, when evaluating your hand, the responder (Bonnie here) uses declarer point count and the NT opener (TJ) uses dummy points count. Bonnie has 8 HCP, + 2 length points, -1 for dubious HQx, + 1 for quality suit, + 1 for side club suit, and + 2 for singleton which is 13 points more than enough to bid 4S. And if spades divide 3-2, it has good plays.|
